[2] Cholera - Cameroon
Date: Tue 14 Sep 2010
Source: CRIENGLISH.com, Xinhua News Agency [summ., edited]
<http://english.cri.cn/6966/2010/09/14/167s594482.htm>


A total of 417 people had been killed by cholera in Cameroon
according to the country's health authorities. The outbreak was
declared on 6 May 2010 in the Extreme-Northern parts of the country
as 6239 cases had been reported.

Apart from spreading to the northern parts of the country, 2
suspected cholera cases have been reported in Yaounde, the country's
capital 3 others in Douala, the country's economic capital.

"These zones are prone to cholera due to heavy rains. Therefore we
should expect to see cholera cases all the time. There are some
carriers who will exhibit cholera symptoms and others who may not, "
the country's Public Health minister Andre Mama Fouda said after a
meeting in his office. He, however, noted that the Extreme Northern
parts, the northern parts, as well as the coastal regions and some
sections of the western region were the most affected by the epidemic.

--
