[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Kano)
Date: Sun 12 Sep 2010
Source: AllAfrica, This Day report [summ., edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/201009130427.html>


Governor Ibrahim Shekarau of Kano State has admitted that cholera,
which has affected some states in the country recently, has also
manifested in 2 local government areas of the state, and cautioned
people in the state to pay more attention to personal hygiene and
environmental sanitation.

The governor, who disclosed the presence of the disease yesterday [11
Sep 2010] in Kano while receiving the [Emir of Kano], who paid him
the traditional Sallah (Islamic celebration) homage at the government
house in Kano, mentioned Kunchi and Bichi as the affected local
governments that the cholera has affected.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Kano State is in the north of Nigeria where most of the cases of
cholera have been occurring. - Mod.LL]

